# Auto detect text files and perform LF normalization
* text=auto

# Files whose SHA256 is pinned somewhere must never be rewritten by git.
#
# `text=auto` stores LF in the object database and restores CRLF on Windows checkout.
# For an ordinary source file that is harmless. For an artifact whose *bytes are its
# identity* -- a frozen registry, a split manifest, a design document mirrored by digest
# -- it is fatal: the checked-out file no longer hashes to the digest recorded inside the
# benchmark manifest, so the integrity check meant to catch tampering fires on a clean
# checkout instead.
#
# `-text` disables newline translation entirely, so these paths round-trip byte-exactly
# on every platform. The writers (benchmark/materialize.py: write_text_lf) emit LF, so
# the bytes are identical everywhere.
results/Benchmark_v0/** -text
results/Benchmark_v0_1/** -text
results/Benchmark_v0_2/** -text
data/benchmark_v0/acquisition_manifest.json -text
docs/benchmark/** -text

# ── 2026-07-14: the same hazard, one layer deeper — **Python source can be digest-pinned too**
#
# `results/Benchmark_v0_2/program_pool.json` pins the SHA256 of the *source files* that
# implement the frozen program pool (`benchmark/programs.py::_POOL_CODE_FILES`):
#   benchmark/programs.py, operators/_common.py, operators/registry.py,
#   operators/s1_denoise.py, operators/s1_outlier.py
# Those are ordinary `.py` files, so they fell under `* text=auto` and were exempt from
# nothing -- meaning a clean Windows checkout restores them with CRLF, their SHA256 changes,
# and every one of those pins goes stale **on an untouched clone**. The pins were computed on
# LF bytes; nothing checked them, so the breakage stayed invisible.
#
# `eol=lf` (rather than `-text`) because it is the stronger guarantee for source: git
# normalizes to LF on the way in *and* checks out LF on every platform, so the working-tree
# bytes are the same everywhere no matter how a contributor's editor is configured.
#
# `tests/test_frozen_action_surfaces.py::test_pool_code_files_are_lf_so_a_clean_checkout_still_hashes`
# enforces this: any pool code file containing CRLF fails the suite.
*.py text eol=lf
